   <titles>
      <title>Rules for Computing with Determinants</title>
      <plain.title>Computing with Determinants</plain.title>
   </titles>
   <intro>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>After learning how to compute the determinant of a matrix, let us now turn to rules for computing with determinants. The essence here is: these rules apply even if we do not know the number value of the determinant of a given matrix. In subsequent sections we will use these rules to discover what a determinant actually means via the concept of ‘oriented volume’. Moreover, we will develop a more efficient method of computing determinants of large matrices.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </intro>
